                <fr:anchor>7415</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IH</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00IH.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="The full relation">The full relation</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>For any two sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, we may form the <fr:em><fr:strong>full <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (A\times  B\right )\mathclose {}}\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } B]]></fr:tex>, also called the <fr:em><fr:strong>total <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:strong></fr:em>, so that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (A\times  B\right )\mathclose {}}}b]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex>. In other words, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (A\times  B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:em>total</fr:em> subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
