                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>7416</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00II</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00II.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="The identity relation">The identity <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>For any set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, we can form the <fr:em><fr:strong>identity <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {id}_{A}\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } A]]></fr:tex>, also called the <fr:em><fr:strong>equality <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:strong></fr:em>, which relates each element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to itself. In other words, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {\mathsf {id}_{A}} a']]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a=a']]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>We have already seen the <fr:link href="jms-00I9.xml" title="Relations in program specification" addr="jms-00I9" type="local">square root relation from positive reals to reals</fr:link>, which corresponds to a <fr:em>total</fr:em> but <fr:em>many-valued</fr:em> function. We can define an analogous relationship in <fr:link href="jms-00IJ.xml" title="The integer square root relation" addr="jms-00IJ" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00IJ" /></fr:link> below from positive integers (naturals) to integers, which will correspond to a <fr:em>partial</fr:em> and many-valued function.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>7417</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IJ</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00IJ.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="The integer square root relation">The integer square root <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>The square root operation corresponds to a relation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R_2\colon  \mathbb {N}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m\mathrel {R_2} n]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m = n^2]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
